WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:04.133
<i>Kids, as you know,
Aunt Robin grew up in Canada.</i>

00:04.133 --> 00:06.434
<i>That meant sometimes she
dressed a little differently.</i>

00:06.434 --> 00:09.067
Okay, let's do this!

00:09.067 --> 00:12.367
<i>Sometimes she talked
a little differently.</i>

00:12.367 --> 00:14.868
Ted, this hydro bill is bigger
than Louis Cyr's biceps.

00:14.868 --> 00:18.000
What, you leave the garburator
on all night, eh?

00:19.300 --> 00:20.901
<i>She hung out at different bars</i>

00:20.901 --> 00:23.000
<i>and enjoyed leisure time
a little differently.</i>

00:23.000 --> 00:26.934
You want to go?
You want to go?! Come on!

00:26.934 --> 00:29.167
Make fun of the Great
White North all you want.

00:29.167 --> 00:30.934
It's the best country
in the world.

00:31.467 --> 00:32.534
The...
Mmmm.

00:32.534 --> 00:33.434
Social experiment.

00:33.434 --> 00:40.033
U.S.A., U.S.A.

00:40.033 --> 00:42.534
Okay, okay.
You know what,

00:42.534 --> 00:43.701
What does that even prove, okay?

00:43.701 --> 00:45.634
You chant anything,
people will join in.

00:45.634 --> 00:49.601
Canada, Canada,

00:49.601 --> 00:51.901
Cana...
Okay, they won't chant anything.

00:51.901 --> 00:54.400
Shrimp fried rice,

00:54.400 --> 00:58.400
Shrimp fried rice,
Shrimp fried rice,

00:58.400 --> 01:00.300
Shrimp fried rice,
Shrimp fried rice...

01:00.300 --> 01:02.868
Shrimp fried rice--
totally.

01:03.834 --> 01:05.601
Anyway, speaking of food,

01:05.601 --> 01:07.133
Marshall, I've got
so bad news.

01:07.133 --> 01:09.067
Just read online,
Gazzola's is closing.

01:09.067 --> 01:10.133
No!

01:10.133 --> 01:11.334
What's Gazzola's?

01:11.334 --> 01:14.901
A filthy mecca of spectacular
if undercooked pizza

01:14.901 --> 01:17.801
located at 316 Kinzie Street,
Chicago, Illinois.

01:17.801 --> 01:20.334
Back in college, Ted and I used
to take these crazy road trips

01:20.334 --> 01:21.868
from Connecticut
all the way to Chicago

01:21.868 --> 01:22.934
Just for a Gazzola's pizza.

01:22.934 --> 01:24.033
22 hours.

01:24.033 --> 01:25.467
No map.

01:25.467 --> 01:27.133
We'd just jump in
the Fiero and drive.

01:27.133 --> 01:28.667
We were like Lewis and Clark,

01:28.667 --> 01:30.801
if Lewis and Clark peed
in empty soda bottles

01:30.801 --> 01:32.801
and had a bong made
out of a cantaloupe.

01:32.801 --> 01:35.334
Man, those Gazzola trips,

01:35.334 --> 01:38.100
that's... that's when
we really became bros.

01:38.801 --> 01:40.367
Mm. We ate nothing
but jerky.

01:40.367 --> 01:41.300
Drank nothing but Tantrum.

01:41.300 --> 01:43.033
<i>Ah, Tantrum.</i>

01:43.033 --> 01:46.334
<i>Tantrum was a soft drink with
the highest caffeine content</i>

01:46.334 --> 01:48.601
<i>legally available
over the counter.</i>

01:48.601 --> 01:49.734
<i>It was eventually discontinued</i>

01:49.734 --> 01:53.133
<i>after an extensive study
by the FDA.</i>

01:55.968 --> 01:59.234
Oh, man, we went through a whole case
of Tantrum one trip.

01:59.234 --> 02:01.767
I was color-blind for
two weeks after that.

02:01.767 --> 02:03.934
I think that's the reason
that I pass out

02:03.934 --> 02:05.834
when I hear church bells.

02:05.834 --> 02:08.032
It's probably a good thing
they're closing Gazzola's.

02:08.032 --> 02:09.667
Those trips were
brutal, right?

02:09.667 --> 02:12.734
The long hours in the car,
the motion sickness, the smell.

02:12.734 --> 02:16.534
So what time are we leaving for Gazzola's tomorrow?
I was thinking 9:00, 9:30.

